text:
♥️ On this sacred day of Eid Mubarak, I wish you blessings and much peace, and may God descend with divine mercy upon the earth, and my heart whispers words destined for you, my love;
My eyes speak to your eyes more deeply than any language I could use. In their gaze, I read my longing, my devotion, and the silent promise I made to you and to myself, a promise that only two souls destined for each other could understand: I love you, I love loving you...
My lips thirst for the water of your spring, and my embrace longs to reunite in your embrace, in the warmth of your love. I will call you a noble knight of the desert, even when the gentle breeze touches your face, I will kiss your face softly with love for many hours on the day of our meeting;
Even if your steps are slow, my beloved, the heart of your beloved follows each one... At the dawn of each day I wait for a message from you, in longing and expectation for the blessing of your voice once more... the poet's voice that loved you forever... And when night falls I find you in dreams, forcing my eyes open because I don't want to wake up already burdened by such great longing... ♥️ @faz3 🙌🏼🙌🏼🌟💎🫀♾️🌙🇦🇪♥️♥️

@faz3  I truly feel this in my heart - I’m deeply worried for our Dubai, my home. 
Holding on to hope for a peaceful resolution and a happy ending for everyone. 
May there be peace in the world ❤️
